text: Rest in Peace, my pal, Peter Chervin. Peter was a one of a kind - a relentless trader and proud father. I had margeritas with him earlier this week in East Hampton's Blue Parrot. He was full of piss and vinegar - laughing and munching the chips and salsa.

And it all ended all too quickly. Its such a short time to be here and a long time to be gone. I will miss yelling at him to go off margin. I will miss his trips to my house in Palm Beach. I am going to miss his friendship and our Monday night dinner at The Palm with Sig.

Yesterday I declined offers to appear by MSNBC's @JoyAnnReid and by CNN's @cuomoprimetime - preferring to stick to investing and letting good investigative reporters like @VickyPJWard do to the "research." The Epstein story will have legs and will likely roil the c suite

and even have political ramifications, imho. Though I relished my days of digging when I was a "Naider Raider" while at Wharton, some things are better left to the professional journalists (and prosecutors) who have already done a wonderful job in exposing the sordid and sleazy
Congratulations to the Final Table at the World Series of Poker Final Event! What a night. And best of luck in the next few days to Palm Beach Kennel's Zhen Cai! wsop.com/2019/
